Plan: Patch block_bind_library to gracefully handle libraries that contain non-binder entries (e.g., a main expression). Remove the strict assertion and skip non-binder entries when binding. This prevents a crash and aligns with the behavior of ignoring non-library definitions while still binding valid function definitions.
